{"body":"# Extract AgentDriver Interface from phase-executor.ts

> **Epic:** Multi-agent backend support
> **Priority:** P0 — all other multi-agent work depends on this

## Context

Sequant's entire headless execution pipeline (`npx sequant run`) is hardcoded to the Claude Agent SDK. The coupling is concentrated in a single file — `src/lib/workflow/phase-executor.ts` — which imports `query` from `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` and uses Claude Code-specific presets:

```typescript
// phase-executor.ts:9-10
import { query } from "@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk";
import type { SDKResultMessage } from "@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk";

// phase-executor.ts:194-195
systemPrompt: { type: "preset", preset: "claude_code" },
tools: { type: "preset", preset: "claude_code" },
```

This blocks support for any alternative agent backend (Aider, Codex CLI, Continue.dev, Copilot SDK, Cursor API).

Additionally, all platform operations (issue fetching, PR creation, comments, labels) are hardcoded to GitHub's \`gh\` CLI across 20+ touchpoints. While full multi-platform support is a separate initiative (#374), this issue should plant the \`PlatformProvider\` seam alongside \`AgentDriver\` so both abstractions ship together as a pure refactor.

## Goal

Extract two interfaces that decouple workflow orchestration from (a) agent execution and (b) platform operations. Claude Code and GitHub become the default implementations; alternatives can be added without touching orchestration logic.

## Acceptance Criteria

### AgentDriver Interface
- [ ] New \`AgentDriver\` interface defined in \`src/lib/workflow/types.ts\` (or a new \`agent-driver.ts\`)
- [ ] Interface exposes at minimum:
  ```typescript
  interface AgentDriver {
    /** Human-readable name for logging */
    name: string;
    /** Execute a phase prompt and return structured result */
    executePhase(
      prompt: string,
      config: AgentExecutionConfig,
    ): Promise<AgentPhaseResult>;
    /** Check if this driver is available/configured */
    isAvailable(): Promise<boolean>;
  }

  interface AgentExecutionConfig {
    cwd: string;
    env: Record<string, string>;
    abortSignal?: AbortSignal;
    phaseTimeout: number;
    verbose: boolean;
    mcp: boolean;
    /** Callback for streaming output */
    onOutput?: (text: string) => void;
    /** Callback for stderr */
    onStderr?: (text: string) => void;
  }

  interface AgentPhaseResult {
    success: boolean;
    output: string;
    sessionId?: string;
    error?: string;
  }
  ```
- [ ] \`ClaudeCodeDriver\` implementation wraps the existing \`query()\` call — no behavior change
- [ ] \`phase-executor.ts\` uses the interface, not the SDK directly
- [ ] Driver selection via \`ExecutionConfig.agent\` field (default: \`"claude-code"\`)
- [ ] CLI wiring: \`--agent <name>\` option in \`bin/cli.ts\` \`run\` command
- [ ] Driver registry pattern (simple map, not a plugin system):
  ```typescript
  const DRIVERS: Record<string, () => AgentDriver> = {
    "claude-code": () => new ClaudeCodeDriver(),
  };
  ```
- [ ] All existing tests pass unchanged (pure refactor)
- [ ] \`@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk\` import only appears in \`ClaudeCodeDriver\`, not in \`phase-executor.ts\`

### PlatformProvider Interface
- [ ] New \`PlatformProvider\` interface defined alongside \`AgentDriver\`:
  ```typescript
  interface PlatformProvider {
    /** Platform name for logging/display */
    name: string;

    /** Issue operations */
    fetchIssue(id: string): Promise<Issue>;
    postComment(issueId: string, body: string): Promise<void>;
    addLabel(issueId: string, label: string): Promise<void>;
    removeLabel(issueId: string, label: string): Promise<void>;

    /** PR operations */
    createPR(opts: CreatePROptions): Promise<PRInfo>;
    getPRStatus(prId: string): Promise<PRStatus>;
    postPRComment(prId: string, body: string): Promise<void>;

    /** Auth and health */
    checkAuth(): Promise<boolean>;

    /** Phase marker operations */
    getIssueComments(issueId: string): Promise<Comment[]>;
  }

  interface Issue {
    id: string;
    number: number;
    title: string;
    body: string;
    labels: string[];
    state: "open" | "closed";
  }

  interface CreatePROptions {
    title: string;
    body: string;
    head: string;
    base: string;
  }

  interface PRInfo {
    number: number;
    url: string;
  }

  interface PRStatus {
    state: "open" | "closed" | "merged";
  }

  interface Comment {
    body: string;
    createdAt: string;
  }
  ```
- [ ] \`GitHubProvider\` implementation wraps existing \`gh\` CLI calls — no behavior change
- [ ] All existing \`gh\` calls consolidated into \`GitHubProvider\` (currently scattered across):
  - \`worktree-manager.ts\` — PR creation (\`gh pr create\`), PR view
  - \`phase-detection.ts\` — issue comment fetching (\`gh issue view --json comments\`)
  - \`pr-status.ts\` — PR status checks (\`gh pr view --json state\`)
  - \`doctor.ts\` — closed issue listing (\`gh issue list --state closed\`)
  - \`system.ts\` — auth checks (\`gh auth status\`)
  - Skills — label management (\`gh issue edit --add-label\`), comment posting (\`gh issue comment\`)
  - \`hooks/pre-tool.sh\` — PR branch detection (\`gh pr view --json headRefName\`)
- [ ] Provider selection via \`ExecutionConfig.platform\` field (default: \`"github"\`)
- [ ] Provider registry alongside driver registry:
  ```typescript
  const PLATFORMS: Record<string, () => PlatformProvider> = {
    "github": () => new GitHubProvider(),
  };
  ```
- [ ] CLI wiring: \`--platform <name>\` option in \`bin/cli.ts\` \`run\` command (default: \`"github"\`)

## Design Considerations

### What stays in phase-executor.ts
- Phase prompt construction (\`PHASE_PROMPTS\`, \`getPhasePrompt\`)
- Cold-start retry logic (\`executePhaseWithRetry\`) — agent-agnostic
- QA verdict parsing (\`parseQaVerdict\`) — output-format-agnostic
- Timeout/abort handling
- Spinner management

### What moves into ClaudeCodeDriver
- The \`query()\` call and message streaming loop (lines 186-258)
- Claude Code-specific options (\`systemPrompt\`, \`tools\`, \`permissionMode\`, \`settingSources\`)
- SDK message type handling (\`SDKResultMessage\`, \`system\`/\`assistant\`/\`result\` types)
- MCP server config injection
- Session resume logic (\`canResume\`, \`resume: sessionId\`)

### What moves into GitHubProvider
- All \`spawnSync("gh", [...])\` calls from \`worktree-manager.ts\`, \`phase-detection.ts\`, \`pr-status.ts\`, \`doctor.ts\`, \`system.ts\`
- GitHub URL pattern extraction (regex for \`github.com/.../pull/\\d+\`)
- GitHub-specific error handling (rate limits, auth failures)
- Repo name validation (currently assumes GitHub format)

### File structure
```
src/lib/workflow/
├── types.ts              # Add AgentDriver + PlatformProvider interfaces
├── phase-executor.ts     # Uses AgentDriver interface (no SDK import)
├── drivers/
│   ├── index.ts          # Driver registry + getDriver()
│   └── claude-code.ts    # ClaudeCodeDriver (owns the SDK import)
├── platforms/
│   ├── index.ts          # Platform registry + getPlatform()
│   └── github.ts         # GitHubProvider (owns all gh CLI calls)
```

### Output normalization
Different agents return different output formats. The \`AgentPhaseResult.output\` field should contain the raw text output. Parsing (QA verdicts, etc.) stays in \`phase-executor.ts\` — the driver just captures text.

### Skills and PlatformProvider
Skills currently embed raw \`gh\` commands. For v1, skills continue to call \`gh\` directly — the \`PlatformProvider\` abstraction covers the orchestration layer (\`phase-executor\`, \`worktree-manager\`, \`phase-detection\`, etc.). Skill platform-awareness is deferred to #374.

## Non-Goals

- No new agent backends in this PR (that's #369+)
- No new platform backends in this PR (that's #374)
- No changes to skill definitions
- No changes to state management schema
- No runtime behavior change — this is a pure refactor with two new CLI flags

## Testing

- Existing \`phase-executor.test.ts\` tests pass with the injected \`executePhaseFn\` pattern (already used for testing)
- New unit test: \`ClaudeCodeDriver\` can be instantiated and \`isAvailable()\` returns true when SDK is importable
- New unit test: driver registry returns correct driver by name, throws on unknown name
- New unit test: \`GitHubProvider.checkAuth()\` calls \`gh auth status\`
- New unit test: platform registry returns correct provider by name, throws on unknown name
- Integration: \`npx sequant run --dry-run\` still works identically","labels":[{"id":"LA_kwDOQzPeLM8AAAACUhtErA","name":"refactor","description":"Code refactoring","color":"fbca04"},{"id":"LA_kwDOQzPeLM8AAAACUl1BaQ","name":"planned","description":"Implementation plan approved","color":"0E8A16"},{"id":"LA_kwDOQzPeLM8AAAACa_U_yw","name":"needs-work","description":"QA found issues that need fixing","color":"e11d48"},{"id":"LA_kwDOQzPeLM8AAAACcQdjCg","name":"multi-agent","description":"Multi-agent backend support and agent-agnostic architecture","color":"7B68EE"}],"state":"OPEN","title":"Extract AgentDriver interface from phase-executor.ts"}

